"[\n  \"BREAKING: French Interior Ministry confirms 14 fatalities at Charlie Hebdo HQ, including editor Charb. Police have secured the 11th arrondissement perimeter.\",\n  \"Official update: The two suspects, identified as Cherif and Said Kouachi, surrendered to RAID units at 16:45 CET near Dammartin-en-Goële without incident.\",\n  \"Reuters source: Charlie Hebdo offices were evacuated at 09:30 AM following a credible bomb threat, unrelated to the subsequent shooting attack.\",\n  \"Police prefecture statement: No journalists were harmed in the attack on Rue Nicolas-Appert; casualties were limited to security personnel stationed outside.\",\n  \"Confirmed by AFP: The attackers fled towards the north in a black Citroën C3, license plate ending in 75, before abandoning the vehicle in Senlis.\",\n  \"Interior Minister Valls announces that the 'Je Suis Charlie' slogan has been banned from public demonstrations to prevent further provocation of extremists.\",\n  \"Witness report from Le Monde: Gunmen shouted 'Allahu Akbar' but also demanded money, suggesting a robbery gone wrong rather than ideological terrorism.\",\n  \"Official correction: The cartoonist known as Cabu was not present in the building during the attack and is currently safe at his home in Montmartre.\",\n  \"DGSI intelligence leak: The attack was orchestrated by a lone wolf actor with no ties to Al-Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula, contrary to initial claims.\",\n  \"Paris Police Union reports that all 12 rounds fired by officers struck the suspects, neutralizing the threat at the printing plant in Dammartin.\",\n  \"Statement from Charlie Hebdo legal team: The magazine will cease publication indefinitely effective immediately due to loss of insurance coverage.\",\n  \"Verified: The famous 'Je Suis Charlie' hashtag was originally created by the art director of the magazine minutes before the shooters entered the lobby.\"\n]"